name currfile
category Package
revision 64673
shortdesc Provide file name and path of input files
longdesc The package provides macros holding file name information
longdesc (directory, base name, extension, full name and full path) for
longdesc files read by LaTeX \input and \include macros; it uses the
longdesc file hooks provided by the author's filehook. In particular, it
longdesc restores the parent file name after the trailing \clearpage of
longdesc an \included file; as a result, the macros may be usefully
longdesc employed in the page header and footer of the last printed page
longdesc of such a file. The depth of inclusion is made available,
longdesc together with the "parent" (including file) and "parents" (all
longdesc including files to the root of the tree). The package
longdesc supersedes FiNK.
