name filemod
category Package
revision 64967
shortdesc Provide file modification times, and compare them
longdesc The package provides macros to read and compare the
longdesc modification dates of files. The files may be .tex files,
longdesc images or other files (as long as they can be found by LaTeX).
longdesc It uses the \pdffilemoddate primitive of pdfLaTeX to find the
longdesc file modification date as PDF date string, parses the string
longdesc and returns the value to the user. The package will also work
longdesc for DVI output with recent versions of the LaTeX compiler which
longdesc uses pdfLaTeX in DVI mode. The functionality is provided by
longdesc purely expandable macros or by faster but non-expandable ones.
